  "text": "The adoption and use of CIT responds to economic incentives and builds on organizational capabilities. As emphasized by prominent observers, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] 28 the long-term benefits of information technology will flow not from the conversion of existing paper data to digital format but, rather, from changes in the ways physicians organize their practices, balance evidence and experience in making clinical decisions, interact with their patients, and are reimbursed for their time and expertise. External incentives such as pay-forperformance and quality improvement programs have the potential to contribute to these important changes in the organization and financing of physician practice.",
